<item>
            <title>[SPR-304] StringTrimmerEditor handles nulls inconsistently</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-304</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue is probably related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-273&quot; title=&quot;Remove check for null when finding custom editors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-273&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-273&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even when emptyAsNull is true, StringTrimmerEditor&apos;s inherited getAsText method returns &quot;null&quot; for a null value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This used to be no problem, as BindException.getFieldValue did not invoke getAsText for null values. But now getAsText is always invoked, even for null values (cf &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-273&quot; title=&quot;Remove check for null when finding custom editors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-273&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-273&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), resulting in &quot;null&quot; being displayed in empty html form fields bound using StringTrimmerEditor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;StringTrimmerEditor should probably override getAsText to return an empty String for a null value when emptyAsNull is true.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
